This paper is primarily focused on image-to-image translation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel and scalable approach for this task, which involves the use of a single model to handle multiple domains. This approach involves the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs), which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of their approach in terms of facial attribute transfer and facial expression synthesis, which are both tasks related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of graphs to illustrate their results, which falls under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of images, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
